    {
      "description": "\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;font color\u003d\u0026quot;red\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;strong\u0026gt;\u0026gt;\u0026nbsp;UK ADVERT, APRIL 1987\u0026lt;/strong\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/font\u0026gt;\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;blockquote\u0026gt;From Personal Computer World magazine.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; Advert said:\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;font color\u003d\u0026quot;#666666\u0026quot;\u0026gt; It\u0027s an extraordinarily powerful machine which offers word-processing, spreadsheet, and a set of time and data-management tools in a single, highly porlable package.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; At \u0026pound;199.95. the Z88 is supplied with 32K resident RAM. Extra 32K costs under \u0026pound;20, extra 128K under \u0026pound;50!\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; And heavy users Will be able to expand the RAM to an astonishing 3 Mbytes, using plug-in RAM cartridges.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; For printing text or data, the Z88 connects direcly to most popular RS232 compatible printers, while for permanent storage the Z88 employs removable solid state EPROM cartridges - no tape to break, no delicate disc to damage.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; Though the Z88 is a powerful, full facility, self-contained computer, it also acts as an extension of an office micro, connecting directly to allow exchange of text or data.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; For every personal computer user, the Z88 offers a comprehensive specification in a package of unparalleled portability.\u0026lt;/font\u0026gt;  \u0026lt;/blockquote\u0026gt;",
